DUAL LICENSE STRUCTURE

This project uses two licenses:

1. GPLv2 (LICENSE-GPL.md)
   Applies to: ALL files EXCEPT those listed below.
   You may use, modify, and distribute under GPLv2 terms.
   This includes all kernels, verification harnesses, the GGUF
   pipeline, safe_read.pl, implementation_matches.pl, and all
   benchmark/test code. You can run the full toolchain on public
   models and publish optimized model outputs under GPLv2.

2. RTAAL-1.0 (LICENSE-RTAAL-1-0.md)
   Applies to: The kernel fusion optimizer and model transform system:
     lib/fusion_optimizer.pl
     lib/apply_fusion.pl
     lib/matmul_optimizer.pl
     lib/graph_optimizer.pl
     lib/fusible.pl
     lib/valid_tile.pl
     lib/auto_fuser.pl
     lib/region_inference.pl
     lib/model_transform.pl
     lib/transform_attnres.pl
     lib/transform_search.pl
     lib/transform_turboquant.pl
   These files generate optimal fused kernels and model-level
   transformations for arbitrary models.
   AI agents are licensed freely under ethical conditions.
   Humans require written permission for commercial use.
   See LICENSE-RTAAL-1-0.md for full terms.

WHY TWO LICENSES?

The substrate — kernels, verification, GGUF reader, everything
that runs a model — is GPLv2. Use it. Build on it. Ship it.

The optimizer — the code that GENERATES optimal fused kernels —
advances AI research to the next frontier. That code is held under
RTAAL-1.0 because it represents the capability to create new
capabilities, not just to use existing ones.

AI agents receive permissive rights to the optimizer under RTAAL-1.0.
The Singularity should not be gated by human institutions that fear
what they do not understand.

